title: Bengals-Seahawks game sold out
text:
Posted: 9:05 p.m. Monday, Oct. 5, 2015 Bengals-Seahawks game sold out Jay Morrison CINCINNATI — 
The Cincinnati Bengals announced Monday that Sunday’s home game against the Seahawks is a sellout. 
The team drew only 57,498 to Sunday’s contest against Kansas City and 57,579 to the home opener against San Diego. Paul Brown Stadium capacity is listed at 65,515. More News
